Software Development/Engineering is still so new that it cannot be agreed upon, whether it even counts as an Engineering discipline or not. So when it comes to the software career ladder, you'll find great variation of role responsibilities across different companies. A few years ago, Developers could has to go into management, and leave 95% of their technical skills behind them, if they wanted to be paid more. This is changing with the idea of the Individual Contributor.
In our company, Team Lead's were responsible for technical direction, delivery and their direct reports. This lead to an incredible work load for the Team Leads, so we decided to experiment with implementing Team and Technical leads within the same team to combat the load. This is how it went (from the Tech Lead's perspective).
